---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Editorial" description="Topology-not-timeline writing on the structure of AI systems.">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 tracking-tight">Editorial</h1>
  <p class="text-lg mb-8 max-w-2xl" style="color: var(--color-ink-dim);">
    Topology, not timeline. Each new piece builds and refines the latent
    structure of AI systems; older pieces don't age out, they become
    foundations for newer ones. All content is primary-source-first and
    linked back to raw material — including the canon envelopes and
    intake items that supplied the evidence.
  </p>

  <p style="color: var(--color-ink-dim);">
    First deep-dives publish once Layer 1 intake has produced enough
    accumulated signal for Layer 2 reasoning to generate candidate claims.
    Areas currently in range:
  </p>
  <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 max-w-2xl">
    <li>
      <strong>The structure of agent harnesses</strong> — Claude Code, Codex CLI, Aider,
      OpenDevin, Cline, and the shape of the thing they all are.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Memory is the next harness moat</strong> — why Letta, mem0, MemGPT, and
      Claude memory don't yet behave alike, and what that tells us about what
      memory <em>is</em> in agent systems.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Context repositories: the pattern emerging under every serious agent team</strong>
      — a worked case study from this very system.
    </li>
  </ul>
</Layout>
